1
00:01:29,450 --> 00:01:33,030
[Cage of Shadows]

2
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:36,229
[Episode 6]

3
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:42,240
You've really screwed me over.

4
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,620
This time, I took it upon myself

5
00:01:43,620 --> 00:01:44,720
and put you two in danger.

6
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:45,520
I'm sorry.

7
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:47,250
You must be out of your mind.

8
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:55,320
What are you doing?

9
00:01:55,620 --> 00:01:56,900
What are you up to now?

10
00:01:58,690 --> 00:01:59,420
Who's there?

11
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:03,160
What are you doing?

12
00:02:08,669 --> 00:02:09,470
Come on.

13
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,300
No, go away.

14
00:02:12,870 --> 00:02:14,030
Don't touch me!

15
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:21,050
What's the point of untying us now?

16
00:02:21,050 --> 00:02:22,579
I shouldn't have trusted you.

17
00:02:22,579 --> 00:02:24,329
Now, my life is threatened because of you.

18
00:02:24,329 --> 00:02:25,250
Dao,

19
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,700
please don't be mad.

20
00:02:26,730 --> 00:02:28,980
Yanzhi must have her own reason
for doing so.

21
00:02:28,980 --> 00:02:30,040
Let me do it myself.

22
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,079
Seriously,

23
00:02:33,079 --> 00:02:34,720
Nan Yanzhi, what exactly is your plan?

24
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:36,120
Right, Yanzhi.

25
00:02:36,140 --> 00:02:37,280
I don't get it either.

26
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:39,500
Why did you reject
the position of champion?

27
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:40,700
Taking that position

28
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:42,310
won't bring us to the third floor.

29
00:02:42,310 --> 00:02:45,850
Didn't they say the champion would receive
a grand reward?

30
00:02:46,590 --> 00:02:48,390
That's indeed what Ms. Qin said.

31
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:00,400
This is the grand reward for the champion.

32
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,360
See for yourselves.

33
00:03:01,110 --> 00:03:02,790
[For the champion]

34
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:10,900
This is...

35
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:12,440
This is poppy.

36
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:14,590
It's mixed with various mushroom powders.

37
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:15,790
You know about herbs?

38
00:03:16,350 --> 00:03:16,950
Yes.

39
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:19,150
I used to collect herbs in mountains
with my grandfather.

40
00:03:19,150 --> 00:03:21,880
So I was exposed to
many types of medicinal herbs.

41
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:23,040
Then what on earth

42
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:25,040
is this thing?

43
00:03:25,060 --> 00:03:26,320
He who takes in too much of this

44
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:28,400
will end up being a walking corpse

45
00:03:28,420 --> 00:03:29,720
like these students.

46
00:03:29,850 --> 00:03:30,770
If that's true,

47
00:03:30,790 --> 00:03:33,430
isn't everyone in the academy
a puppet of Ms. Qin's?

48
00:03:33,430 --> 00:03:34,360
That's right.

49
00:03:34,890 --> 00:03:37,340
Good thing we didn't team up
with those two girls.

50
00:03:37,340 --> 00:03:39,420
Or we would be trapped here forever.

51
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:42,630
Ms. Qin spends every day
with these puppets.

52
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:44,240
Doesn't she find it creepy?

53
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,440
Perhaps some people are just

54
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:47,480
glad to indulge themselves in illusions

55
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:50,140
and to enjoy such kind
of delusional happiness.

56
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:53,240
Then those people are hopelessly stupid.

57
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,940
The more joyful they are in the dreams,

58
00:03:54,940 --> 00:03:56,700
the more miserable they feel
as they wake up.

59
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:57,680
If it were me,

60
00:03:57,920 --> 00:03:59,710
even under severe torture, I'd still

61
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:00,900
stand on my feet with a clear head.

62
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:02,780
Trying to make me eat this kind of stuff?

63
00:04:02,780 --> 00:04:03,620
No way!

64
00:04:03,830 --> 00:04:04,830
How dare you!

65
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,430
Who let you in?

66
00:04:09,450 --> 00:04:10,890
Some people talk about

67
00:04:11,170 --> 00:04:12,710
morals and righteousness all the time.

68
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:14,710
However, look at what they've done.

69
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,490
They shouldn't be teachers at all.

70
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:18,510
Since I took charge of the academy,

71
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:19,860
I've never met

72
00:04:19,890 --> 00:04:21,899
students as unruly as you lot.

73
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:24,400
It seems like someone's asking
to learn her lesson

74
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,620
the hard way.

75
00:04:31,710 --> 00:04:32,740
Officer Qin!

76
00:04:34,159 --> 00:04:35,180
What did you call me?

77
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:36,220
"Officer Qin."

78
00:04:44,730 --> 00:04:45,930
After so many years,

79
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:48,020
I can't believe
someone's calling me that again.

80
00:04:48,020 --> 00:04:48,800
Officer Qin,

81
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:51,360
you were once the most reputed
lady of talent in the dynasty.

82
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:54,120
You once managed imperial decrees
for the Empress Dowager

83
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:56,480
with the power to draft edicts
and command all officials.

84
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,080
Am I wrong for addressing you

85
00:04:58,330 --> 00:04:59,330
as "Officer Qin"?

86
00:05:01,430 --> 00:05:03,300
You revealed my true identity.

87
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:05,440
Aren't you afraid that I might kill you?

88
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:07,700
Of course you could kill me, Officer Qin.

89
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,080
But before my life ends,

90
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,040
I have a question

91
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,840
for the once most talented lady,
who, in everyone's eyes,

92
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,960
was kind and fully committed
to the people.

93
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:15,840
Does she...

94
00:05:16,470 --> 00:05:17,640
still exist?

95
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,880
She already died.

96
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:31,590
I'd rather grow old clinging
to a fragrant branch

97
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,940
than dance with yellow leaves
in the autumn wind.

98
00:05:33,940 --> 00:05:35,520
This famous quote was written

99
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,480
by Officer Qin at her rite of passage.

100
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,120
If the old her were dead,

101
00:05:39,140 --> 00:05:41,800
how could I have won
the championship this time?

102
00:05:43,030 --> 00:05:44,500
What else do you know?

103
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:45,920
It's said that she was gifted
to the Crown Prince

104
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,620
since the Empress Dowager fell from grace.

105
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:49,620
Nobody has heard from her thereafter.

106
00:05:49,620 --> 00:05:51,440
That said, exactly

107
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,960
because of Officer Qin, many women

108
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:54,080
were admitted to academies.

109
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:55,040
They got to learn,

110
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,159
to break free from traditional dogmas,

111
00:05:56,159 --> 00:05:57,260
and to make a living for themselves.

112
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:58,380
Up to this day,

113
00:05:58,409 --> 00:05:59,340
in their hearts,

114
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:02,070
Officer Qin is still
the most talented woman

115
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:04,220
and an excellent female chancellor.

116
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:09,520
I hate for my talent in poetry
to be concealed by pretty gowns.

117
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:12,360
Looking up, I can only admire
the chosen scholars on the list.

118
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,820
So what if I used to be
the most talented lady?

119
00:06:14,930 --> 00:06:17,390
Without the Empress Dowager's protection,

120
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:20,480
I was simply a plaything
decorated with gold and jade.

121
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:23,660
Once such a woman
falls into the hands of men,

122
00:06:24,060 --> 00:06:26,300
all her talent becomes useless.

123
00:06:26,410 --> 00:06:28,670
They don't care about her gift in poetry.

124
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,600
All they care about

125
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,800
is the body hidden

126
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,960
beneath her thin clothes.

127
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,400
What a shame.

128
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,400
I blame my young self
for being too arrogant

129
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,860
and conceited due to my talent back then.

130
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:45,070
Stay away from me!

131
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:48,720
I will never sleep
with a good-for-nothing like you!

132
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:51,070
I demand to see the Crown Prince!

133
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,920
I demand to see the Crown Prince!

134
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:25,810
I considered myself noble and refused

135
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,400
to please men with my beauty.

136
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:32,440
I even drew a cut across that man's neck.

137
00:07:34,350 --> 00:07:36,010
However, the Crown Prince...

138
00:07:37,010 --> 00:07:38,780
He determined that I was guilty

139
00:07:39,490 --> 00:07:41,150
and threw me into prison.

140
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:42,830
Only then did I realize

141
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,520
that he wasn't interested in me at all.

142
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:48,440
He only meant to eliminate
an important aide
to the Empress Dowager.

143
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:50,380
Without the latter's protection,

144
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:52,260
I was reduced to a prisoner

145
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:54,080
trampled upon by anyone at will.

146
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:57,240
Even the lowest of the low could abuse me.

147
00:08:05,710 --> 00:08:06,710
At that moment,

148
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,200
all my talent,

149
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:10,890
all my learning,

150
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:13,040
and all my loyalty,

151
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:15,260
became a joke.

152
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,520
Then, Officer Qin,

153
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:25,910
how did you end up here?

154
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,200
I thought I would be tortured to death

155
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,530
and thrown into the mass grave.

156
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:32,240
But noticing my proficiency in medicine,

157
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:34,039
the master of Lingya Tower bought me,

158
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:35,700
so I could help him test drugs.

159
00:08:37,059 --> 00:08:38,200
Do you know

160
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:40,220
you're aiding the evil?

161
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:43,640
This tower is filled with sins.

162
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,800
So what?

163
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:47,700
I stopped caring about morality
a long time ago.

164
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:50,320
At least, here, I have my academy

165
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,690
and my students.

166
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,730
I can be a teacher and impart knowledge

167
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,120
at this place.

168
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,760
This is not an academy at all.

169
00:08:59,780 --> 00:09:01,550
And those are not your students.

170
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:03,760
They're all manipulated
by that bell of yours!

171
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:05,790
You're drowned in your own illusion.

172
00:09:05,790 --> 00:09:08,790
How are you any different
from those walking corpses?

173
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,130
So what if this is just an illusion?

174
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:16,080
My life is already shattered and ruined.

175
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,320
All I want to do is stay in my own dream

176
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:21,160
that transcends the mundane.

177
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:24,260
What's wrong with idling the rest

178
00:09:24,690 --> 00:09:26,490
of my life away in a lovely dream?

179
00:09:29,790 --> 00:09:31,560
That slap was to wake you up,

180
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:32,440
Officer Qin.

181
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:34,700
A woman though you are,

182
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:35,800
you unconventionally and bravely

183
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,750
broke the chains of traditional doctrines.

184
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,560
You have what it takes
to govern the country

185
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:41,290
and the ability to strategize.

186
00:09:41,470 --> 00:09:43,800
Yet now you've willingly degraded yourself

187
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:46,160
into a lackey
for the exploitative privileged!

188
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,840
Easy for you to say that.

189
00:09:49,110 --> 00:09:50,350
I'm in a living hell

190
00:09:50,380 --> 00:09:51,690
with no strength to climb up.

191
00:09:51,690 --> 00:09:53,040
Even if I hate all of this,

192
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:54,280
what can I do?

193
00:09:55,690 --> 00:09:56,880
My life is worthless.

194
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:58,150
What can I do?

195
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,590
If you do hate all of this,

196
00:10:01,050 --> 00:10:02,910
then fight till your last breath,

197
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,160
kill those vile people,

198
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:05,200
leave this living hell,

199
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,800
and lead a decent life again!

200
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,280
You really are interesting.

201
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:24,880
Tell me.

202
00:10:25,370 --> 00:10:26,670
After all this hustle,

203
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,720
what exactly do you want?

204
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,530
I want the antidote.

205
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,080
Ms. Qin,

206
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:50,480
I've always been curious about one thing.

207
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,780
How did the previous captives

208
00:10:51,780 --> 00:10:53,540
make it past the second floor?

209
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,240
It's actually quite simple.

210
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:59,200
As long as you manage to come here
at midnight,

211
00:10:59,740 --> 00:11:01,890
a mute servant will take you
to the third floor.

212
00:11:01,890 --> 00:11:02,960
It's that simple?

213
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:06,400
I've imposed a strict curfew in here.

214
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,260
Do you think everyone else is like you?

215
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:09,330
I see.

216
00:11:16,850 --> 00:11:19,660
If you find it impossible to stay
on the third floor anymore,

217
00:11:19,660 --> 00:11:21,520
you are always welcome back here.

218
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:33,050
I'm not sure if it's right
to bring you with me.

219
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,360
You put on quite an act.

220
00:11:53,340 --> 00:11:54,480
You told her my true identity,

221
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,400
didn't you?

222
00:11:56,870 --> 00:11:58,000
I don't understand.

223
00:11:58,780 --> 00:12:00,600
I invited you time and again before,

224
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:02,040
yet you never responded.

225
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:04,840
Why did you open your heart

226
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:07,270
to her this time?

227
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,360
I bet you're not

228
00:12:08,730 --> 00:12:10,930
making this visit for the Tower Master,

229
00:12:11,060 --> 00:12:12,260
but for her, right?

230
00:12:16,370 --> 00:12:18,000
I will report to the Tower Master

231
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,530
that there is nothing wrong

232
00:12:20,890 --> 00:12:22,220
with the Elite Academy.

233
00:12:23,130 --> 00:12:24,210
Wait a moment!

234
00:12:26,620 --> 00:12:28,800
You said you would help me kill

235
00:12:28,820 --> 00:12:30,440
the person who put me in prison.

236
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:31,440
Do you mean it?

237
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:34,960
We both know

238
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:36,340
that person holds immense power.

239
00:12:36,340 --> 00:12:37,470
If you want revenge,

240
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:40,360
we must work together.

241
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:41,640
Fine.

242
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,320
If you help me,

243
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:44,910
I will help her.

244
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:11,850
[The Third Floor of Lingya Tower]

245
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:11,060
What crummy place is this?

246
00:13:11,710 --> 00:13:14,560
Isn't each floor supposed to be better
than the last?

247
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:16,960
This looks even worse
than the first floor.

248
00:13:17,140 --> 00:13:19,470
What kind of match awaits us
on this floor?

249
00:13:19,570 --> 00:13:22,170
Are the three of us
the only participants here?

250
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:42,420
Have you heard...

251
00:13:47,460 --> 00:13:48,860
any unusual sounds?

252
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:49,640
Yes.

253
00:13:52,670 --> 00:13:55,630
Sounds like a blacksmith shop.

254
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:58,460
What exactly is this match about?

255
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:02,320
What is this match about?

256
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:04,610
Is it really just among the three of us?

257
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:07,240
Why bother talking to the mute servant?

258
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:09,880
Filling our stomaches
is the priority now.

259
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,130
The food is indeed better than before.

260
00:14:13,530 --> 00:14:14,330
Hold on.

261
00:14:30,390 --> 00:14:32,190
How dare you poison the food?

262
00:14:32,220 --> 00:14:33,760
What on earth are you people trying to do?

263
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:34,670
Seems like

264
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:38,220
we'll either be poisoned
or starved to death on this floor.

265
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,410
No wonder there's no one else here.

266
00:14:41,010 --> 00:14:42,630
Take us to the voice-keeper.

267
00:14:46,130 --> 00:14:48,190
[First Meeting]

